</section>

<section>
	<h4 class="example example-sentence example-example">Good personal healthcare includes diet and nutrition, exercise, preventative care, and having regular checkups with a physician. <span class="red">FAULTY PARALELLISM!</span></h4>
	<p class="example example-explanation example-explanation">This example is similar to the last in that it places an action in a sequence of objects. The difference between this example and the last is that in this example our action, "having regular checkups with a physician", does in fact have parallel meaning with the other items in the list. They are all included as things that contribute to good personal healthcare. To fix it, we will have to address the form of our final item.</p>
	<h4 class="example example-corrected example-corrected">Good personal healthcare includes diet and nutrition, exercise, preventative care, and regular checkups with a physician. <span class="green">CORRECT!</span></h4>
	<p class="example corrected-explanation example-corrected-explanation">To correct the faulty parallelism in our example, we convert the final item in the list from an action to a noun by dropping the verb "having". This gives our list proper parallel structure.</p>
	<button class="btn btn-large btn-primary example-button">Show Example</button>
</section>

<section>
	<h4 class="example example-sentence example-example">The patient asked the doctor about the drug's side effects, dosage regimen, and listed their past medications. <span class="red">FAULTY PARALLELISM!</span></h4>
	<p class="example example-explanation example-explanation">Once more we see an example of faulty parallelism in which an action is given parallel structure with a set of nouns to which it is not parallel in meaning. We can correct this by separating the action from the set of nouns.</p>
	<h4 class="example example-corrected example-corrected">The patient asked the doctor about the drug's side effects and dosage regimen and listed their past medications.<span class="green">CORRECT!</span></h4>
	<p class="example corrected-explanation example-corrected-explanation">We correct our sentence by removing the action "listed their past medications" from the list of nouns relating to the drug and placing it in parallel structure with the other action the patient took "asked the doctor". This fixes the faulty parallelism and gives us a complete sentence.</p>
